# testdata/invoices/ holds the M4-11 synthetic invoice fixture set, emitted
# byte-for-byte by tools/fixturegen and byte-compared against regeneration
# by tools/fixturegen's TestCommittedFixtures_MatchRegeneration guard (see
# tools/fixturegen/committed_test.go). One fixture (edge_bad_encoding.csv)
# is intentionally UTF-16LE and several use bare \n line endings to
# exercise parser edge cases -- any git-side EOL or encoding normalization
# on commit/checkout would silently corrupt those bytes and make CI's
# checked-out copy diverge from what the guard regenerates in-memory,
# failing the guard for a reason that has nothing to do with the code
# under test. -text opts the whole directory out of git's text handling
# (no EOL conversion, no encoding reinterpretation) so every checkout,
# on every OS, gets the exact bytes that were committed.
testdata/invoices/** -text
